-- Louis Dreyfus Commodities Signs $800 Million Loan Facility
-- B y   L o u i s e   M e e s o n
-- 2011-12-20T10:30:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-20/louis-dreyfus-commodities-signs-800-million-loan-facility.html
Louis Dreyfus Commodities Suisse SA ,
the raw materials trader with roots going back to 1851, signed
its first European syndicated loan facility.  The $800 million three-year financing, guaranteed by parent
company Louis Dreyfus Commodities B.V., is split between a term
loan and revolving credit facility, according to a statement
from lenders. The deal was increased from $600 million, the
lender said.  HSBC Holdings Plc, BNP Paribas SA and UniCredit SpA were
among a 28-strong group of lenders involved in the deal.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Louise Meeson in London at 
